Was the sound of your heart beating beneath your skin.

In your love, I found the shape of my own.
And now, in every path I claim as mine,
I carry your strength, your fire, your spine.

Posted @withregram • @amitaggarwalofficial What if beauty was never in the fabric or the walls, but in the hands that chose to transform what was into what could be?

At Amit Aggarwal, pre-loved Banarsi sarees are reimagined into silhouettes that speak of strength, transformation, and becoming.

And at Garima Greh, Rudrani Chhetri (@rudranichhetri @mitrtrust ) builds more than a home—she redefines what it means to belong, offering safety, dignity, and pride to the transgender community.

Beauty doesn’t resist change, it evolves through it.
They gather what the world once cast aside.
Unraveling what was, to imagine what can be.
And in that becoming—we find each other.

For @amitaggarwalofficial In the folds of time and tradition, 
family is where everything begins and belongs.
Moments held close, hands held tighter—a connection that outlasts trends, a bond that defines eternity.

There’s a quiet metamorphosis in a love so deep,
where laughter lingers, and stories steep.

Here, presence becomes the purest gift. 
Hearts mirror each other, and love is not linear—it’s layered, luminous, and ever-evolving.
